2020-08-03  Levente Mészáros

	Updated all registerService, registerProtocol methods and calls.

2020-09-03  Andras Varga

	Removed ulong, as its size is platform-dependent (on Windows, long=int32!)

2020-09-02  Andras Varga

	Renamed packet -> tcpSegment and tcpseg -> tcpHeader, for clarity.

2020-09-01  Andras Varga

	Removed code to withhold last, fractional segment if there's more data in
	the send buffer. See #558.

	I have not found an explicit statement about this in the RFCs. However, I
	found pcap traces of TCP file transfers (e.g. tcp-ethereal-file1.trace on
	https://wiki.wireshark.org/SampleCaptures), which contain several
	instances of a burst of full-size segments followed by a fractional one,
	which indicates that this change is probably right.

2020-08-31  Andras Varga

	Updating state->snd_max moved into sendSegment()

2020-08-28  Andras Varga

	Removed state->sentBytes, converted to retval of sendSegment().

	It was only used immediately after a sendSegment(), and contained the
	payload length in the segment just sent. This is better done with
	sendSegment()'s return value.

2020-08-25  Andras Varga

	Fixed #558: Nagle was not obeyed for data > MSS sent (credit: Marius Poke)

2020-06-04  Zoltan Bojthe

	Added new statistic tcpRcvPayloadBytes to TcpConnection: amount of payload
	bytes received (including duplicates, out of order etc) for TCP throughput.

2020-06-03  Marcel Marek

	Added signal/statistics for rcvdPayloadBytes

