2014-03-19  ------ inet-2.3.0 released ------

2014-03-15  Thomas Dreibholz

	TCP: queue size limitation

	- By default, the TCP behaviour remains unchanged.
	- If queue limit is set by the TCP_C_QUEUE_BYTES_LIMIT command,
	  the TCP model gives an indication to the application when it should
	  generate more data.

	This patch is helpful when comparing SCTP and TCP behaviour.

